  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A gene is a segment of [DNA](./dna.md) that encodes the information needed to produce a functional product — usually a protein, sometimes a functional RNA molecule. Genes are the units of heredity: they are passed from parent to offspring through reproduction, and the variation among genes within a population is the material on which [natural selection](../../adaptation/terms/natural-selection.md) acts.",
  "keywords": "biology, genetics",
